## Celebrating a Decade Dedicated to Development : ABP is 10 Years Old!

Today is not just another day. Today, we celebrate a decade of dedication, innovation, and collaboration. A decade ago, the seeds of a vision were sown with the first commit to the open-source [ASP.NET Boilerplate](https://aspnetboilerplate.com/) project. As we stand at this significant milestone, let's take a moment to reflect on our journey.
Milestones Through the Decade
August 2013: The journey began with the first commit to the open-source ASP.NET Boilerplate project.
February 23, 2014: We celebrated the first official release of ASP.NET Boilerplate, marking its readiness for the developer community.
May 17, 2015: The launch of ASP.NET Zero provided a startup solution based on the foundational ASP.NET Boilerplate.
December 4, 2016: A new chapter unfolded with the first commit to the open-source ABP Framework project, taking forward the legacy of ASP.NET Boilerplate.
June 27, 2018: The first release of the ABP Framework showcased its capabilities and features.
September 24, 2018: We publicly announced the open-source ABP Framework project, inviting developers worldwide to be a part of this journey.
January 15, 2020: The introduction of ABP Commercial added a layer of commercial benefits and features on top of the robust ABP Framework.
August 18, 2023: Today, we celebrate the 10th birthdate of the ABP project!

Celebrating with Our Community
To commemorate this special occasion, we've planned a series of celebrations:
A reflective blog post detailing our journey, challenges, successes, and learnings.
A 10% discount on every license purchase for the next six months.
A special anniversary banner on our website, celebrating our decade-long journey.
Regular announcements on Twitter, keeping the celebration alive and engaging our community.

A Big Thank You!
Our journey over the past decade wouldn't have been possible without you - our dedicated community of developers, contributors, partners, and users. Your feedback, support, and trust have been the driving force behind every milestone we've achieved.
Looking Ahead
While we cherish our achievements over the past decade, we're even more excited about the future. With your continued support, we're committed to pushing the boundaries, innovating, and ensuring that ABP remains the go-to framework for developers worldwide.
Here's to the past ten years of innovation, collaboration, and success. And here's to many more decades of excellence!
